<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
 <head>
  <title>CSS Floats: Auto Sizing Float Followed By Text</title>
  <style type="text/css">
   .control { display: inline; font: 1em/1 Ahem, sans-serif; background: red; color: white; }
   container { display: block; width: 100px; background: red; color: green; font: 50px Ahem; position: relative; }
   float { float: left; color: white; }
  </style>
 </head>
 <body>
  <div class="control">Ahem_font_required_for_this_test.</div>
  <p>There should be a green square below this line.</p>
  <container xmlns="http://www.w3.org/">
   <float>X</float>X
  </container>
 </body>
</html>
